            Primark shoppers 'ecstatic' at reopening
            More than 1,000 people queued outside the new Primark store in Belfast when its doors opened on Saturday.Crowd control measures, including crush barriers, were in place outside the new store at Commonwealth House, which opened at 09:00 GMT.The retailer has returned to the city four months after a huge fire destroyed its flagship store at Bank Buildings in August."It's like Christmas coming early - I'm ecstatic," said one shopper.Read more here.
                
                        08 Dec 2018
                    
                
        
